   **GLOBAL FIX:**
   
   To prevent this type of bug, it would be better to use an iterative solution
   for the Fibonacci function, which does not use recursion and thus does not
   risk exhausting the stack.
   
   ```c
   int fib(int n) {
     if (n <= 1) return n;
     int a = 0, b = 1;
     for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
       int temp = a;
       a = b;
       b = temp + b;
     }
     return b;
   }
   ```
   
   This solution has the same time complexity as the recursive solution, but
   uses a constant amount of stack space.
